  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And on the other hand, she, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] she got married virtually 10 days after she arrived in the United States.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And she became a housewife and a mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And peculiarly enough, my sister Izabella, who was the performer, so to say, eventually became the writer and has published several books on the Holocaust, including a children's book for ages eight and nine, which is supposed to be the only one directed at, so far, at that age level and has been a tremendous success.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Her others, two books, have been translated into half a dozen languages and certainly part of every Holocaust course and library.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "My sister Regina was always sought out for her recitation of poetry, even to the point where, in fairly dark days already, at the Hungarian national independence day, I suppose you would call it, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] despite the fact that she was a Jew, she was invited to recite the great national hymn or, or anthem at the public observance.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Reciting poetry was, in those days in Hungary, as in other parts of Europe, was considered a great art.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] That is probably the most difficult for myself and, and for my sisters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My youngest sister was about 13 or going on 13 when we arrived in Auschwitz and was sent [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to her death with my mother.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It has been probably the most difficult thing for us to endure because having been the youngest, we all doted on her.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We all, each and every one of us, we always catch ourselves talking and thinking and feeling about her as though she was our child, every one of us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We each claim, so to say, to be the parent.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
